cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about human pose estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel method for learning scale-aware representations, which involves training a neural network, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses high-resolution feature pyramids, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed method in crowded scenes, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) applications.
